description: Returns a list of events for a specific database in Amazon Lightsail.

parameters.name: relationalDatabaseName
parameters.description: The name of the database from which to get events.

parameters.name: durationInMinutes
parameters.description: The number of minutes in the past from which to retrieve events. For example, to get all events from the past 2 hours, enter 120. Default: 60 The minimum is 1 and the maximum is 14 days (20160 minutes).

parameters.name: pageToken
parameters.description: The token to advance to the next page of results from your request. To get a page token, perform an initial GetRelationalDatabaseEvents request. If your results are paginated, the response will return a next page token that you can specify as the page token in a subsequent request.

nested_items.name: relationalDatabaseEvents
nested_items.description: An object describing the result of your get relational database events request.

nested_items.name: resource
nested_items.description: The database that the database event relates to.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp when the database event was created.

nested_items.name: message
nested_items.description: The message of the database event.

nested_items.name: eventCategories
nested_items.description: The category that the database event belongs to.

nested_items.name: nextPageToken
nested_items.description: The token to advance to the next page of results from your request.
